                        <!--  *************************************  <handDesc>  ********************************* -->

                        <handDesc hands="1">
                            <handNote ana="#molded">The text is generally without many noteworthy
                                features. There appears to be an interpunct between the two lines
                                set in the middle of the dish, though this may be a feature of the
                                casting. The letters are generally evenly spaced apart, with the
                                exception of the first L of Licinius, which could potentially be set
                                further apart to draw the eye to the beginning of the circular
                                inscription. The N of Naissus does have a slight blemish, possibly a
                                complication of casting </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

