    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="outer_circle">
                    <ab> 
                        <lb n="1"/><persName type="imperial"><name type="gentilicium" key="Licinius">Licini</name> <name type="cognomen" key="Augustus">Auguste</name></persName>, semper vincas!
                    </ab>
                </div>                    
                <div type="textpart" subtype="in_corona">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="2"/>Sic <num type="cardinal" value="10">X</num> <supplied reason="subaudible">annis</supplied>,
                    <lb n="3"/>sic <num type="cardinal" value="20">XX</num>.
                </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="stamp">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="4"/><placeName><expan><abbr>Na
                        <lb n="5" break="no"/>iss</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan></placeName> <supplied reason="subaudible">fecit</supplied>.
                    </ab>
                </div>
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>“Licinius Augustus, may you always be victorious! As for 10 (years), so for 20.
                    Naissus (dedicated this).”</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text notes the commemoration made in Naissus of the emperor Licinius’ 10th
                    year of reign, which allows for a precise dating of 317 CE. This is one of
                    several such dishes which were produced in honor of this anniversary</p></div>
            

